cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is about comparing different classification algorithms on real-life binary datasets. The focus is on machine learning and data analysis, which suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, the use of datasets related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) also make these sub-categories likely. Additionally, the use of Bayesian ANOVA analysis and neural networks (mentioned in the abstract) suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
